data.name: Pickled Cauliflower
data.quickTastyDescription: A crunchy and tangy side dish that adds a zesty flavor to any meal!
detailedCookingInstructions: In a pot, combine vinegar, water, sugar, and salt. Bring to a boil.
Once boiling, remove from heat and add garlic, black peppercorns, mustard seeds, coriander seeds, and red pepper flakes.
Place the cauliflower florets in a clean jar or container.
Pour the hot vinegar mixture over the cauliflower until fully submerged.
Let it cool to room temperature, then seal and refrigerate for at least 24 hours before serving.
data.modifiersForBase: Add various spices for different flavors
